Vol / Page: 17
Edition:
Quote: If the newly-located settlers made and effort to get a supply of seed of the uwhi, a winter potato generally grown by the Maoris in the north, they would find this much to their advantage... The uwhi, a  large round pink potato, is a far more abundant cropper than the ordinary kidney potato.
